<body><p>GE.10-16428 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Fifteenth session 
</b>Agenda item 2 
<b>Annual report of the United Nations High Commissioner 
for Human Rights and reports of the Office of the  
High Commissioner and the Secretary-General 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Algeria</b>*<b>, Bangladesh, Cuba, Nigeria, Syrian Arab Republic</b>*<b>, Venezuela (Bolivarian 
Republic of)</b>*<b>: draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>  15/&#8230; Strengthening dialogue, coordination and cooperation between  
 the Human Rights Council and the Office of the United Nations  
 High Commissioner for Human Rights 
</b></p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i>Recalling </i>General Assembly resolution 48/141 of 20 December 1993, in which the 
Assembly, inter alia, decided that the United Nations High Commissioner for Human 
Rights shall be the United Nations official with principal responsibility for United Nations 
human rights activities under the direction and authority of the Secretary-General, and 
within the framework of the overall competence, authority and decisions of the General 
Assembly, the Economic and Social Council and the Commission on Human Rights, 
</p>
<p><i>Recalling also</i> General Assembly resolution 60/251 of 15 March 2006, in which the 
Assembly, inter alia, decided that the Human Rights Council should assume the role and 
responsibilities of the Commission on Human Rights relating to the work of the Office of 
the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights, as decided by the Assembly in 
its resolution 48/141, 
</p>
<p><i>Recalling further</i> General Assembly resolutions 62/246 of 3 April 2008 and 64/243 
of 24 December 2009, 
</p>
<p><i>Recalling </i>its resolution 5/1 of 18 June 2007 entitled &#8220;Institution-building of the 
United Nations Human Rights Council&#8221;, 
</p>
<p><i>Reaffirming</i> that the General Assembly, the Economic and Social Council and the 
Human Rights Council are the organs responsible for decision- and policy-making for the 
promotion and protection of all human rights, 
</p>
<p>  
 * Non-Member State of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>

<p><i>Recalling</i> regulations 4.8 and 4.9 and rule 104.6 of the Regulations and Rules 
Governing Programme Planning, the Programme Aspects of the Budget, the Monitoring of 
Implementation and the Methods of Evaluation, 
</p>
<p>1. <i>Affirms </i>that strengthened dialogue, coordination and cooperation between the 
Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights and the Human Rights 
Council contributes to better synergy in the work of the United Nations human rights 
machinery and consequently to the improvement and effectiveness of activities in the 
promotion and protection of human rights; 
</p>
<p>2.<i> Welcomes</i> the efforts of the High Commissioner to strengthen dialogue, 
coordination and cooperation with the Council, Member States and civil society in areas 
relevant to the work of the Office of High Commissioner; 
</p>
<p>3.<i> Recalls<b> </b></i>all relevant General Assembly, Council and Commission on Human 
Rights resolutions which provide mandates relevant to the work of the Office of the High 
Commissioner, and affirms the importance of such resolutions being taken fully into 
account by the Office in planning its activities and in preparing its proposed contribution to 
the strategic framework under programme 19; </p>
<p>4. <i>Requests </i>the High Commissioner to formally present proposals for the human 
rights programme of all future strategic frameworks for the consideration of the Council, 
and to consider<b> </b>the views and comments of Member States and relevant stakeholders in the 
preparation of such an important document before it is submitted to the Committee for 
Programme and Coordination and the General Assembly. 
</p>
<p>  </p>

